law.text: An otherwise eligible worker under this chapter shall be ineligible for benefits for any week in a benefit year unless, subsequent to the beginning of the worker's immediately preceding benefit year, he or she returned to work and earned wages in covered employment equal to at least five (5) times his or her weekly benefit rate established for the previous benefit year.
law.history: Created 2011 Ky. Acts ch. 30, sec. 1, effective June 8, 2011.
